    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect security header type in NR NAS deregistration request\n\n### Summary\nThe `generateDeregistrationRequest` function in NR UE NAS was using an inappropriate security header type for the inner message, causing unexpected behavior when sending NAS detach requests. This fix corrects the security header type to follow 3GPP specifications.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/NR_UE/nr_nas_msg_sim.c`: Changed the inner message security header type from `INTEGRITY_PROTECTED_AND_CIPHERED_WITH_NEW_SECU_CTX` to `PLAIN_5GS_MSG` in the `generateDeregistrationRequest` function (line 746).\n\n### How to Reproduce\nWhen calling `send_nas_detach_req()` function, the UE would exhibit unexpected behavior during deregistration procedures. The network might reject the deregistration request or handle it incorrectly due to the inappropriate security header type that was only meant for SECURITY MODE COMPLETE messages according to 3GPP TS 24.501.\n\nThe fix ensures that the deregistration request follows the same pattern as other NAS messages in the codebase, using `PLAIN_5GS_MSG` for the inner message while maintaining proper integrity protection through the outer message security header.\n"
}